    "Name": "Grand Crusader",
    "Details": "The first production model of the Grand Crusder. A 240 XL engine propels the 'Mech to a top speed of 54.0 km/h, while still leaving enough weight capacity for a balanced design. The Grand Crusader is protected by 15.5 tons of armor and, to handle the 'Mech's heat burden, the Grand Crusader carries 10 double heat sinks. The Grand Crusader is well-armed to engage an enemy at medium to long ranges. The primary long-range weapons are a pair of LRM-20 launchers fed from a combined six ton of ammunition, mated with an Artemis IV fire control system for greater missile accuracy. For medium range combat, the Grand Crusader has two Large Pulse Lasers and, for close range combat, the 'Mech has two Medium Pulse Lasers. For added protection against missile attacks, the Grand Crusader carries an AMS, mounted on a pivot point on top of the cockpit.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Stable</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.14</color></b>\n\n<br><br><color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Upper, Right Upper</color>",
